00:24:58.040 --> 00:24:59.334
Now back to the story.

00:25:01.246 --> 00:25:03.474
Steve, we're now
getting back to your island.

00:25:03.541 --> 00:25:05.480
Getting back to Chokoloskee Island.

00:25:05.547 --> 00:25:10.143
Many a load of weed has been along
this beach right here in these houses.

00:25:10.910 --> 00:25:12.779
-What was your place here? Which one?

00:25:12.846 --> 00:25:15.116
The one with the truck backed up to it.

00:25:15.183 --> 00:25:16.474
-Oh, that one.
-Yeah

00:25:16.541 --> 00:25:19.326
That ain't the original house
but that was my house.

00:25:19.393 --> 00:25:22.769
We filled that garage up
I can't tell you how many times.

00:25:22.836 --> 00:25:25.671
You gotta remember
we brought in millions of pounds.

00:25:26.220 --> 00:25:28.236
-So what about hurricanes now?

00:25:28.303 --> 00:25:30.905
-Everybody's used to them.
-You're just used to them.

00:25:30.972 --> 00:25:34.159
Where my place is I'm above it.
I don't get none of it.

00:25:34.226 --> 00:25:37.275
-But right here I mean…
-They get flooded pretty close.

00:25:37.342 --> 00:25:39.733
But the house is lifted up and off.

00:25:39.800 --> 00:25:42.173
-Yeah but they still get flooded.
-Yeah.

00:25:42.240 --> 00:25:43.713
Steve, I always ask this

00:25:43.780 --> 00:25:46.305
because there people
that don't live in the South.

00:25:46.372 --> 00:25:49.043
The Confederate flag,
what's it mean to you?

00:25:49.110 --> 00:25:51.434
Well my
great-great-great-great-grandfather

00:25:51.501 --> 00:25:53.733
fought for the Confederacy in Fort Ogden.

00:25:53.800 --> 00:25:56.612
He was with the Calvary so it's history.

00:25:57.315 --> 00:26:01.339
You know, them wanting to do away with all
the monuments and stuff,

00:26:01.926 --> 00:26:02.856
it's just history.

00:26:02.923 --> 00:26:06.603
They're just doing away with history.
You can't you can't rewind it.

00:26:06.670 --> 00:26:08.011
It was part of the past.

00:26:08.460 --> 00:26:10.610
Let it be and let it stay.

00:26:11.533 --> 00:26:13.733
Look how far the tides rose.

00:26:13.800 --> 00:26:15.388
-Oh yeah they came up a lot.

00:26:19.053 --> 00:26:21.176
Pete, I've enjoyed myself. What about you?

00:26:21.250 --> 00:26:23.343
-Oh yeah, no, that was awesome Steve.

00:26:23.410 --> 00:26:25.351
Hey I got my first kiss from her.

00:26:26.280 --> 00:26:28.791
I've just been under
the water hose. It was so hot.

00:26:28.858 --> 00:26:30.433
This is your first kiss?

00:26:30.500 --> 00:26:32.010
My first kiss I got from her.

00:26:32.077 --> 00:26:33.313
Was that last night?

00:26:33.380 --> 00:26:35.913
No, it's been a long time ago.

00:26:35.980 --> 00:26:37.828
-Chubby-cubby.
-That was a long time.

00:26:37.895 --> 00:26:40.219
How many generations
has your family been here?

00:26:40.286 --> 00:26:42.113
Six generations.
Six?!

00:26:42.180 --> 00:26:44.528
-Do you miss the early '80s?
-Oh yeah.

00:26:44.595 --> 00:26:45.782
That was just fun.

00:26:45.849 --> 00:26:47.319
-That was awesome.
-Wasn't it?

00:26:47.386 --> 00:26:48.894
Everyone's flush with cash.

00:26:48.961 --> 00:26:52.056
She was married to
one of the biggest smugglers around.

00:26:52.123 --> 00:26:54.237
There was three main groups,

00:26:54.858 --> 00:26:57.454
and her husband was one of the main…

00:26:58.033 --> 00:26:59.707
I'll let her finish telling it.

00:26:59.774 --> 00:27:02.153
He was just… little big man.

00:27:02.793 --> 00:27:05.063
-Was there a clash
between the three groups?

00:27:05.130 --> 00:27:06.034
No.

00:27:06.101 --> 00:27:08.816
-You guys all got along?
-We all got along pretty much.

00:27:08.883 --> 00:27:10.214
Everybody split the money.

00:27:10.281 --> 00:27:14.149
-I was telling about Everglades people.
-We didn't like the Everglades people.

00:27:14.216 --> 00:27:17.027
We wouldn't even let them
come and play pool at the bar.

00:27:17.094 --> 00:27:18.779
-Really?
-Mm-hmm.

00:27:18.846 --> 00:27:19.729
What about now?

00:27:20.737 --> 00:27:23.530
Everybody's everybody now. Things changed.

00:27:23.950 --> 00:27:27.243
Getting to be almost 70.
I don't care anymore.

00:27:27.310 --> 00:27:30.181
A lot of locals live here.
Everybody came back home.

00:27:30.248 --> 00:27:31.976
I moved away and I just came back.

00:27:32.043 --> 00:27:34.485
-Where'd you go to?
-I went up to LaBelle area.

00:27:34.947 --> 00:27:36.111
Why'd you come back?

00:27:36.178 --> 00:27:37.861
-I miss this place.
-Miss home.

00:27:37.928 --> 00:27:40.378
You come across the bridge
and you smell that mud?

00:27:40.445 --> 00:27:42.104
-That's home.
-It's in your blood?

00:27:42.171 --> 00:27:45.053
-Everyone else is like, woo.
-I'll say one more thing.

00:27:45.120 --> 00:27:47.127
My daughter's 20 years old now.

00:27:47.627 --> 00:27:51.333
When she comes over the bridge
in Chokoloskee she rolls her windows down.

00:27:51.400 --> 00:27:53.200
That's it. You gotta smell that mud.

00:27:53.267 --> 00:27:55.538
She goes, [sniffs] "Daddy, I smell home."

00:27:55.605 --> 00:27:57.883
-You're home. Saltwater, man.
-Exactly.

00:27:57.950 --> 00:28:00.443
-Just no place like this place.
-Right, special.

00:28:00.510 --> 00:28:02.507
We played hide-and-go-seek in the water

00:28:02.574 --> 00:28:06.470
'Cause we had boats and motors.
Nobody had bicycles and things like that.

00:28:06.538 --> 00:28:08.283
We had fun all the time.

00:28:08.350 --> 00:28:09.761
People were poor

00:28:09.828 --> 00:28:13.387
and when they took the mullet fishing away
what else were they gonna do?

00:28:13.454 --> 00:28:15.190
You know, that was our livelihood.

00:28:15.681 --> 00:28:19.962
And they took it away and somebody
offered you money to haul some weed in…

00:28:20.029 --> 00:28:20.912
Hell yeah.

00:28:20.979 --> 00:28:23.556
I mean we're notorious for rum and gators

00:28:23.623 --> 00:28:27.603
and bird plumes, and, you know,
we're gonna do the next best thing.

00:28:29.166 --> 00:28:31.586
[Steve] Hey Ramona, I'mma back out.

00:28:31.653 --> 00:28:32.536
All right.

00:28:33.240 --> 00:28:35.668
So Steve, you said
you wanted to make it clear

00:28:35.735 --> 00:28:37.139
you're not doing boat tours.

00:28:37.206 --> 00:28:39.178
I'm not doing boat tours.
That's a joke.

00:28:39.245 --> 00:28:40.453
-It's a joke?
-Yeah.

00:28:40.520 --> 00:28:41.646
But I will…

00:28:41.713 --> 00:28:44.380
If I got somebody that goes on my buggy

00:28:44.999 --> 00:28:47.121
and they want to play around and go see it

00:28:47.188 --> 00:28:49.796
I'll take them.
I won't charge them nothing.

00:28:49.863 --> 00:28:52.773
If they wanna pay for the fuel
that's up to them.

00:28:52.840 --> 00:28:55.423
For those that don't know,
didn't see Steve before,

00:28:55.490 --> 00:28:58.818
I met Steve out on his buggy.

00:28:59.573 --> 00:29:00.876
And people loved him.

00:29:00.943 --> 00:29:02.849
That's why we're here again today.

00:29:02.916 --> 00:29:04.952
And I'm gonna leave Steve's link below.

00:29:05.019 --> 00:29:07.113
You want the buggy tour,
the history tour?

00:29:07.180 --> 00:29:10.638
-You want people calling you?
-Sure. Call me anytime.

00:29:10.705 --> 00:29:14.755
-You like the phone?
-The best time is between 6:00 and 9:00.

00:29:14.822 --> 00:29:16.823
-I go to bed early.
-East Coast. Okay.

00:29:16.890 --> 00:29:19.773
Listen if you can't afford a buggy tour

00:29:20.428 --> 00:29:23.113
you're having a hard time,
struggling, call me.

00:29:23.180 --> 00:29:25.260
I'mma make sure you go.

00:29:25.680 --> 00:29:29.834
-I'm not gonna leave you stranded.
-You sure you want the lineup out the door?

00:29:30.343 --> 00:29:34.637
If a person can't afford it and they want
to see the Everglades, I gotta help them.

00:29:34.704 --> 00:29:36.389
-I got to.
-Okay.

00:29:36.456 --> 00:29:39.110
And then the people
that can afford it, tip big right?

00:29:39.177 --> 00:29:40.386
-Tip.
-Tip.

00:29:40.453 --> 00:29:42.648
If you enjoy it give us a tip.

00:29:42.715 --> 00:29:43.741
Okay.

00:29:43.808 --> 00:29:45.447
So let me…

00:29:45.514 --> 00:29:47.326
Have you been on Steve's buggy tour?

00:29:47.393 --> 00:29:51.323
I have not been on Steve's buggy tour
but I heard it's really good.

00:29:51.390 --> 00:29:54.418
I'm too busy running the motel,
and marina, and the restaurant.

00:29:54.485 --> 00:29:56.408
I don't have time to do the fun stuff.

00:29:56.475 --> 00:30:00.255
-We're gonna your restaurant right?
-Yeah. Best restaurant on the island.

00:30:00.322 --> 00:30:02.972
-Is it the only restaurant?
-It's the only restaurant.

00:30:03.039 --> 00:30:05.506
They don't mean nothing
just 'cause it's the only.

00:30:05.573 --> 00:30:08.683
It's the best restaurant
as far as I'm concerned.

00:30:08.750 --> 00:30:12.066
-You guys just feel like
you're in your own little isolated world?

00:30:12.133 --> 00:30:13.034
Pretty much yeah.

00:30:13.101 --> 00:30:15.553
Cut off from
the rest of Florida, the country.

00:30:15.620 --> 00:30:16.503
Yeah.

00:30:16.570 --> 00:30:18.752
We get like three good months of a bunch of

00:30:18.819 --> 00:30:21.368
Northerners or tourists that come down and

00:30:21.435 --> 00:30:24.172
let us know that we do live in paradise.

00:30:24.239 --> 00:30:28.293
We do appreciate y'all. We love y'all.
Don't get it wrong. Don't get it twisted.

00:30:28.360 --> 00:30:30.623
Nobody's coming in the summer right?

00:30:30.690 --> 00:30:31.658
Just the diehards.

00:30:31.725 --> 00:30:35.319
The mosquitoes are bad but
the fishing's great and there's nobody here

00:30:35.386 --> 00:30:37.674
and you don't have to fight the crowds.

00:30:37.741 --> 00:30:39.256
German tourists in the summer?

00:30:39.323 --> 00:30:40.810
Tons of Germans.

00:30:40.877 --> 00:30:42.035
They love this stuff.

00:30:42.102 --> 00:30:44.675
They love suffering. Right?

00:30:44.742 --> 00:30:46.313
I think it's in their history.

00:30:46.380 --> 00:30:49.153
-They go to Death Valley in the summers.
-Yeah.

00:30:49.220 --> 00:30:51.641
It gets like 110 degrees down here.

00:30:51.708 --> 00:30:53.723
A hundred percent humidity and…

00:30:53.790 --> 00:30:57.496
-That's why I look so young.
-[Steve] Hard to believe you're 68.

00:30:57.563 --> 00:30:58.563
[trim motor hums]

00:31:01.568 --> 00:31:02.980
[jeep engine starts]

00:31:06.924 --> 00:31:08.166
Here you go, Steve.

00:31:08.233 --> 00:31:10.833
Thank you, Peter. Thank you very much.

00:31:11.516 --> 00:31:13.516
-Up to your place?
-Up to my place.

00:31:14.428 --> 00:31:18.357
You're gotta love that.
Just roll down windows, everything simple.

00:31:18.424 --> 00:31:19.793
-No problem.
-Simple gauges.

00:31:19.860 --> 00:31:22.700
Holes in the floor
for the water to run out.

00:31:22.767 --> 00:31:23.650
Oh right.

00:31:23.717 --> 00:31:25.658
-Yeah.
-There you go. Look at that.

00:31:27.191 --> 00:31:29.342
-I like that old tractor.
-That is cool.

00:31:29.409 --> 00:31:31.993
This right here
is the highest point on the island.

00:31:32.060 --> 00:31:34.423
-Oh here's your place.
-Here's my place.

00:31:35.220 --> 00:31:38.396
Hey Pete is there a wood block
over there by that tree?

00:31:39.300 --> 00:31:43.015
-Yep.
-Would you mind grabbing that for me?

00:31:43.814 --> 00:31:45.362
Under the tire? Oh right here?

00:31:45.429 --> 00:31:47.558
I'm gonna put it right underneath here.

00:31:49.599 --> 00:31:51.072
Come on, Peter.

00:31:51.830 --> 00:31:53.169
I like detailing.

00:31:53.236 --> 00:31:54.343
You can tell.

00:31:54.410 --> 00:31:56.078
Here's all my detail stuff.

00:31:56.594 --> 00:31:59.513
I keep it in containers
where it don't get wet.

00:32:00.061 --> 00:32:02.315
So that's it.

00:32:02.930 --> 00:32:04.393
-So this is the place.

00:32:04.460 --> 00:32:07.481
-This is the crib, Steve.
-This is it. This is where I sleep.

00:32:07.548 --> 00:32:09.900
I give my master bedroom to my son.

00:32:10.600 --> 00:32:12.533
-Is that you?
-That's me.

00:32:12.600 --> 00:32:13.964
-That's me and my daughter.

00:32:14.031 --> 00:32:16.090
-How old were you?
-Seven years ago.

00:32:16.969 --> 00:32:19.743
This is me and my family.

00:32:20.630 --> 00:32:21.924
That's the son I lost.

00:32:22.393 --> 00:32:23.593
-Okay.
-Okay.

00:32:23.660 --> 00:32:27.641
This is my father, really my grandfather,
but my father and me.

00:32:28.600 --> 00:32:32.076
This is my great-grandfather.

00:32:32.143 --> 00:32:35.272
Remember I told you across the river
from the Rod and Gun Club?

00:32:35.339 --> 00:32:36.677
That's over there.

00:32:36.744 --> 00:32:40.204
The very first tours
in the Everglades National Park.

00:32:40.763 --> 00:32:41.973
That's the boat.

00:32:42.040 --> 00:32:44.190
-He was giving the first tours?
-Very first.

00:32:44.257 --> 00:32:48.468
I'm the very first to do it
in the Big Cypress National Preserve.

00:32:48.535 --> 00:32:49.633
Very first.

00:32:49.700 --> 00:32:50.890
This is my closet.

00:32:52.180 --> 00:32:53.298
This is my kitchen.

00:32:54.490 --> 00:32:56.290
You've got the fishing rods in here.

00:32:56.357 --> 00:32:58.973
-Ready to go at all times Steve?
-Ready to go. Yep.

00:32:59.040 --> 00:33:00.687
Then you can walk back here.

00:33:04.350 --> 00:33:07.518
This was my son's truck when he got killed.

00:33:08.370 --> 00:33:09.253
Um…

00:33:10.230 --> 00:33:13.465
I had to pay off truck and get it.
It means a lot to me.

00:33:14.009 --> 00:33:16.105
My son was 41 years old.

00:33:16.713 --> 00:33:19.014
He was killed by a driver, an old man.

00:33:19.503 --> 00:33:20.833
He has a son.

00:33:20.900 --> 00:33:23.843
His ex-wife has a son.

00:33:24.640 --> 00:33:28.376
And I just want to say,
people, hug your kids

00:33:29.507 --> 00:33:31.804
every day and tell them you love them.

00:33:32.261 --> 00:33:35.862
Because the last words
that I spoke to my son

00:33:36.447 --> 00:33:37.727
was I love you, son.

00:33:38.328 --> 00:33:39.870
And he said I love you, dad.

00:33:39.937 --> 00:33:41.562
He was like my right arm.

00:33:42.488 --> 00:33:44.133
I woke up this morning

00:33:45.140 --> 00:33:48.309
and there was a thing
on Snapchat I think it was.

00:33:48.376 --> 00:33:50.788
And I don't look at that stuff very much.

00:33:50.856 --> 00:33:53.723
And it said Adam and his friends.

00:33:53.790 --> 00:33:57.866
And it had a picture of him
and I looked at it and there was a video

00:33:58.533 --> 00:34:00.701
of him by his airboat.

00:34:02.103 --> 00:34:04.077
And his son was sitting on the airboat,

00:34:04.144 --> 00:34:07.013
and he said,
"Alright, I'm coming to the camp.

00:34:07.080 --> 00:34:08.611
See you later, Naples."

00:34:10.100 --> 00:34:11.909
And I cried for 30 minutes.

00:34:11.976 --> 00:34:13.391
-This morning?
-This morning.

00:34:13.458 --> 00:34:17.039
I cried for 30 minutes. I couldn't stop.

00:34:19.030 --> 00:34:20.311
Because of my son.

00:34:20.378 --> 00:34:24.863
But I know like I said on the last video
that God has needed him.

00:34:24.930 --> 00:34:28.514
'Cause he was a good man,
a good Christian.

00:34:28.581 --> 00:34:30.588
He's up there. They built an army.

00:34:31.066 --> 00:34:35.256
God's gotta fight. Things are going wrong
in this country in this world.

00:34:35.330 --> 00:34:36.843
So God's gotta fight.

00:34:36.910 --> 00:34:39.141
He's taken the young people.

00:34:39.208 --> 00:34:42.368
Because I know he's lost
two or three of his best buddies

00:34:42.435 --> 00:34:44.606
have gone his age up there.

00:34:44.673 --> 00:34:46.999
So love your sons. Love your kids.

00:34:47.690 --> 00:34:50.558
But let's go look at my… shop.

00:34:53.260 --> 00:34:55.788
Excuse me. It's awful messy.

00:34:56.512 --> 00:34:57.885
But this is my shop.

00:34:58.566 --> 00:35:00.873
And I really love it.

00:35:00.940 --> 00:35:02.743
We take really good care of it.

00:35:02.810 --> 00:35:03.967
All my drills.

00:35:05.370 --> 00:35:08.958
All my tools, I've got more tools
than most people could ever…

00:35:09.590 --> 00:35:14.188
All VEVOR stuff, and I'm not blocking
for VEVOR but I'm gonna tell ya,

00:35:14.255 --> 00:35:16.683
they're some of
the best tools I've ever used.

00:35:16.750 --> 00:35:19.303
And they're half the price of normal tools.

00:35:19.370 --> 00:35:22.413
So you're fixing,
'cause we're gonna get out at the end.

00:35:22.480 --> 00:35:25.288
-We're getting out to your buggy operation.
-Yeah.

00:35:25.355 --> 00:35:28.005
That's a whole different way
of seeing the Everglades.

00:35:28.072 --> 00:35:30.943
-Yes. Whole different way.
-I can see one right here.

00:35:31.010 --> 00:35:34.398
This is one that's not complete
or you use it for parts?

00:35:34.465 --> 00:35:37.297
-No. This is gonna be.
Oh I wanted to say something.

00:35:37.364 --> 00:35:42.093
I've got a GoFundMe account
for a handicap buggy.

00:35:42.160 --> 00:35:44.513
-I'm trying to build a handicap buggy.
-Okay.

00:35:44.586 --> 00:35:48.656
So that's what this is. This was donated
to me for starting on my handicap buggy.

00:35:48.730 --> 00:35:51.537
-Okay. So you want to bring
handicapped people out there.

00:35:51.604 --> 00:35:52.613
Free!

00:35:52.680 --> 00:35:53.582
-Free?
-Free!

00:35:53.649 --> 00:35:56.376
I want to build
a wheelchair ramp on this buggy

00:35:56.450 --> 00:35:59.063
to get people in wheelchairs up here.

00:35:59.130 --> 00:36:00.983
-Okay. GoFundMe for that.

00:36:01.050 --> 00:36:02.156
Yeah. Please.

00:36:02.223 --> 00:36:05.233
-And 100% of that money goes to this?
-A hundred percent!

00:36:05.300 --> 00:36:07.777
There's a wheelchair ramp
that a guy donated to me

00:36:07.844 --> 00:36:10.771
and we're gonna use parts
off of them to make one.

00:36:10.838 --> 00:36:12.359
What's driving you to do that?

00:36:12.426 --> 00:36:14.801
Why do you want to bring
handicapped people out?

00:36:14.868 --> 00:36:16.780
My heart. My heart.

00:36:16.847 --> 00:36:18.579
I got calls from people.

00:36:18.646 --> 00:36:22.657
"Hey Captain Steve, I'm in a wheelchair,
could I get up on your buggy?

00:36:22.724 --> 00:36:24.632
I'm going I don't have a way to do it.

00:36:24.699 --> 00:36:27.319
But I can tell you what I have done.

00:36:27.386 --> 00:36:29.963
I've called the National Park Rangers

00:36:30.030 --> 00:36:32.231
and four or five of them
will come out there

00:36:32.298 --> 00:36:34.805
and help lift me up on the buggy.

00:36:34.872 --> 00:36:37.045
For free. Don't charge them nothing.

00:36:37.112 --> 00:36:38.771
Right now if you're handicapped

00:36:39.343 --> 00:36:41.270
we'll get you up on the buggy.

00:36:41.337 --> 00:36:43.800
All of us… The park will come help me.

00:36:43.867 --> 00:36:46.476
But the problem is
if I break down or something

00:36:46.543 --> 00:36:47.954
you know you got to get off.

00:36:48.021 --> 00:36:50.400
You want the ultimate
handicapped buggy machine.

00:36:50.467 --> 00:36:51.761
Yeah. If I got a ramp

00:36:52.570 --> 00:36:54.219
that goes up and down

00:36:54.932 --> 00:36:58.070
if I break down I can lift the ramp
and they can roll across

00:36:58.137 --> 00:36:59.913
to get on another buggy.

00:36:59.980 --> 00:37:01.392
It's gonna be very safe.

00:37:01.863 --> 00:37:04.029
But you just never know.
You use a buggy

00:37:04.932 --> 00:37:07.957
in that mud and water and every day

00:37:08.024 --> 00:37:09.341
you get break downs.

00:37:09.408 --> 00:37:10.467
You can't help it.

00:37:12.267 --> 00:37:14.424
-Steve these banyan trees
are beautiful huh?

00:37:14.491 --> 00:37:17.819
Oh ain't they? You gotta
keep cutting them roots boy, if you don't…

00:37:17.886 --> 00:37:19.429
-If you don't, what happens?

00:37:19.496 --> 00:37:21.073
You see what happens.

00:37:21.140 --> 00:37:23.611
-They just take over.
-They go into a tree.

00:37:24.186 --> 00:37:28.975
[Peter] Yeah. They're like
in their own ecosystems, these trees.

00:37:31.679 --> 00:37:35.629
This is the old Ted Smallwood's home,
the original home.

00:37:35.696 --> 00:37:37.883
He owned the whole island at one time.

00:37:37.950 --> 00:37:39.929
He owns the Smallwood store and museum.

00:37:39.996 --> 00:37:42.387
That's his home. That's his original house.

00:37:42.454 --> 00:37:43.351
-Gotcha.

00:37:43.424 --> 00:37:46.580
-That's a little teeny thing.
Little teeny thing.

00:37:47.930 --> 00:37:52.783
And here is the world famous Havana cafe.

00:37:53.300 --> 00:37:54.477
-This is Aaron's place?

00:37:54.544 --> 00:37:57.924
-This is Aaron's and David's. All right.

00:37:58.623 --> 00:38:00.917
[Brown Eyed Girl by Van Morrison plays]

00:38:01.890 --> 00:38:03.213
Do you smoke cigars?

00:38:03.280 --> 00:38:05.221
-I don't. No. Do you?
-No.

00:38:05.288 --> 00:38:06.585
I got one here.

00:38:06.652 --> 00:38:10.080
They had a Cuban guy
rolling them and I got one.

00:38:10.147 --> 00:38:12.829
I thought I might smoke it.
I thought, nah, better not

00:38:12.896 --> 00:38:16.778
'cause it might take me back to the days
when I was a cigar smoker.

00:38:17.740 --> 00:38:19.811
-This is a cool place.
-Yes.

00:38:22.119 --> 00:38:23.865
-David.
-Hey how's it going?

00:38:23.932 --> 00:38:26.079
How are you doing, David?

00:38:26.146 --> 00:38:29.446
Thanks for coming all the way down
in the middle of the Everglades.

00:38:29.513 --> 00:38:31.363
-The middle of everything.
-That's it.

00:38:31.430 --> 00:38:34.371
This is where
the 10,000 islands end and Everglades

00:38:35.339 --> 00:38:36.521
keeps on keeping on.

00:38:36.588 --> 00:38:39.634
-You did an amazing job with this place.
-You think so?

00:38:39.701 --> 00:38:40.676
It looks beautiful.

00:38:40.743 --> 00:38:43.365
We're lucky
because it's been here for over 20 years.

00:38:43.432 --> 00:38:44.582
Okay. So you bought it?

00:38:44.649 --> 00:38:47.082
Yeah we started in the pandemic.

00:38:47.731 --> 00:38:49.682
Right after they let it go.

00:38:49.749 --> 00:38:52.263
-Aaron grew up here. 
-Where'd you grow up?

00:38:52.330 --> 00:38:56.053
Aaron's outside. I was on the East Coast
and I came to Everglades City

00:38:56.120 --> 00:38:58.107
but I never knew about Chokoloskee.

00:38:58.607 --> 00:39:02.093
And that was where I was like
during the pandemic I was like what?

00:39:02.627 --> 00:39:06.141
Chokoloskee? It's across the bay
and you gotta come across the causeway

00:39:06.208 --> 00:39:08.836
which is like old Florida vibes.

00:39:08.903 --> 00:39:11.004
-It's super cool.
-Are you loving it?

00:39:11.071 --> 00:39:13.190
Yeah. It's living our best life down here.

00:39:13.257 --> 00:39:14.531
We got the island breeze.

00:39:14.598 --> 00:39:18.297
It's a way the Florida Keys
used to be back in the '70s and '80s.

00:39:18.843 --> 00:39:22.098
Small-town vibes.
Everyone knows everybody.

00:39:22.571 --> 00:39:23.612
It's real.

00:39:23.679 --> 00:39:25.633
The night sky is glorious.

00:39:25.700 --> 00:39:29.332
Plus all these species of migrating sh*t
comes through here all the time.

00:39:29.400 --> 00:39:31.869
Oh! Fishing is good year-round.

00:39:31.936 --> 00:39:35.612
You got different things going on.
You got birds. I love it.

00:39:35.679 --> 00:39:36.755
-Are you the chef?

00:39:36.822 --> 00:39:38.163
I do the best I can.

00:39:38.230 --> 00:39:41.313
Yes sir. Yes sir. Perfect man. Thanks.

00:39:41.380 --> 00:39:43.077
-Thank you.
-Come back anytime.

00:39:43.544 --> 00:39:45.968
-Aaron…
-Welcome to Havana Cafe.

00:39:46.035 --> 00:39:48.534
-Wow this is your other hat you wear?
-Oh yeah.

00:39:48.601 --> 00:39:49.724
Wow look at this.

00:39:49.791 --> 00:39:51.903
Let me turn it around. Okay now I'm ready.

00:39:51.970 --> 00:39:54.634
This is wild, man.
This is such a cool zone.

00:39:55.184 --> 00:39:56.220
Peter!

00:39:56.287 --> 00:39:58.381
No way, dude! [laughs]

00:39:59.015 --> 00:40:01.009
[Peter] I've been looking for you.

00:40:01.076 --> 00:40:03.452
I've been waiting for this day for years.

00:40:03.519 --> 00:40:05.579
-No way!
-It's come brother.

00:40:05.646 --> 00:40:07.368
Can I take a picture with you?

00:40:07.435 --> 00:40:08.657
-What's your name?
-Nick.

00:40:08.724 --> 00:40:10.910
Nick, what do you think of Chokoloskee?

00:40:10.977 --> 00:40:13.527
It's my favorite place.
If it wasn't for your video,

00:40:13.594 --> 00:40:16.055
one, my wife and I wouldn't have came here.

00:40:16.122 --> 00:40:18.056
We just moved to Florida from Indiana.

00:40:18.123 --> 00:40:20.424
We watched your video
while I was in Indiana.

00:40:20.491 --> 00:40:23.250
-Are you serious?
-I said I have to go there.

00:40:23.967 --> 00:40:26.415
-I'm gotta take a picture with you.
-Let's do it.

00:40:26.482 --> 00:40:27.468
This is crazy.

00:40:27.535 --> 00:40:30.335
I'm doing a video with Steve.
I don't know where he went.

00:40:30.403 --> 00:40:34.227
I just saw him. I told him 
I just saw you in a YouTube video too.

00:40:35.000 --> 00:40:36.186
You're loving it?

00:40:36.253 --> 00:40:39.583
I love it. I watched your video
with when you went to the Glades.

00:40:39.650 --> 00:40:41.443
-With Harrison.
-Harrison. Yep.

00:40:41.510 --> 00:40:44.006
And I was like, oh that place looks sick.

00:40:44.073 --> 00:40:45.747
So we came down here.

00:40:45.814 --> 00:40:47.682
I got lost with my daughter.

00:40:47.749 --> 00:40:50.149
-Can I put the camera on her?
-Yeah yeah totally.

00:40:50.215 --> 00:40:51.187
Okay.

00:40:51.254 --> 00:40:53.963
Came down here with my daughter. Got lost.

00:40:54.030 --> 00:40:57.146
I was like, I've seen this place before.
It was in your video.

00:40:57.213 --> 00:40:59.753
And then ever since
we've been coming every week.

00:40:59.820 --> 00:41:01.570
We're selling the house in Indiana.

00:41:01.638 --> 00:41:04.974
And my wife's family is in Marco Island.

00:41:05.749 --> 00:41:09.180
So we've been bouncing around,
we're probably gonna end up in Naples.

00:41:09.247 --> 00:41:11.824
But yeah, this whole area, dude, I love it.

00:41:11.891 --> 00:41:14.959
I wouldn't have known about this area
if it wasn't for your video.

00:41:15.026 --> 00:41:15.943
I'm not kidding.

00:41:16.010 --> 00:41:18.347
-You're in one now. You're in it.
-That's crazy.

00:41:18.414 --> 00:41:20.389
These are your kids? These are my kids.

00:41:20.456 --> 00:41:22.258
-This is my sister.
-Oh nice.

00:41:22.325 --> 00:41:23.903
-How's the music?
-Incredible.

00:41:24.833 --> 00:41:26.009
[Peter] The Manzies?

00:41:26.076 --> 00:41:27.558
[Playing Wagon Wheel]

00:41:28.372 --> 00:41:29.405
Thank you.

00:41:31.677 --> 00:41:32.560
Nick…

00:41:32.627 --> 00:41:35.345
You also did a video
in my hometown, Gary, Indiana.

00:41:35.412 --> 00:41:37.612
-That's your hometown.
-That's where we left.

00:41:37.679 --> 00:41:40.207
-Did I do it right or no?
-You did it perfect.

00:41:40.670 --> 00:41:42.494
-No, you did it perfect.
-Okay cool.

00:41:43.370 --> 00:41:45.203
-Take care, Nick.
-You too.

00:41:46.658 --> 00:41:49.839
Aaron is this your guy's touch
or you guys bought it like this?

00:41:49.906 --> 00:41:53.253
Oh the trees were here
but we put all the fun stuff in there.

00:41:53.320 --> 00:41:54.275
-That's so cool.

00:41:54.342 --> 00:41:56.577
-The birds we didn't put in there but…

00:41:57.523 --> 00:42:01.316
You know the great thing about restaurants,
they're super easy businesses.

00:42:01.383 --> 00:42:02.333
-Right?
-Yeah.

00:42:02.400 --> 00:42:03.451
-Not?
-No.

00:42:03.519 --> 00:42:05.903
-That's what we do.
-You do it? Hard, huh?

00:42:05.970 --> 00:42:08.333
They're like,
"Buy a restaurant. It'll be fun."

00:42:08.400 --> 00:42:10.363
"It'll be fun. Buy a restaurant."

00:42:11.010 --> 00:42:12.446
You're here on a break.

00:42:12.513 --> 00:42:13.790
-You're a nurse?
-Yeah.

00:42:14.224 --> 00:42:17.040
And you're like
I just wanna chill out, for a little bit.

00:42:17.107 --> 00:42:18.473
Taking a nice little break.

00:42:18.540 --> 00:42:20.716
-What's better money, this or nursing?

00:42:21.496 --> 00:42:24.930
I would say in about six hours here

00:42:24.997 --> 00:42:28.393
I make about the same
that I would in a 12-hour shift nursing.

00:42:28.460 --> 00:42:31.081
-Are you serious?
-[Aaron] They make good money here.

00:42:31.148 --> 00:42:35.147
It depends on the day. We definitely
get busy and it does get stressful here.

00:42:35.214 --> 00:42:36.853
You missed the lunch rush.

00:42:36.920 --> 00:42:40.132
Every day from 11:00 to 2:00
we always have like plenty of people

00:42:40.199 --> 00:42:42.781
-So I guess it's the only game in town.
-Yeah.

00:42:42.848 --> 00:42:45.186
We do have a few places
down in Everglades City

00:42:45.253 --> 00:42:47.933
but on Chokoloskee
this is the only restaurant.

00:42:48.000 --> 00:42:51.337
[Aaron] Stone Crabs, hush Puppies, oh yeah.

00:42:51.827 --> 00:42:54.103
We are the world capital of stone crabs

00:42:54.170 --> 00:42:56.773
and we have
the best hush puppies on the island.

00:42:56.840 --> 00:42:58.004
-What are Hush Puppies?

00:42:58.071 --> 00:42:59.713
-Hush Puppies. Good question.

00:42:59.780 --> 00:43:01.262
What are Hush Puppies Steve?

00:43:01.735 --> 00:43:05.473
-They're a local local thing
they got corn and…

00:43:05.540 --> 00:43:07.483
[Peter] These guys, hush puppies.

00:43:07.550 --> 00:43:09.159
There's for your shells.

00:43:09.226 --> 00:43:11.293
I don't want no crabs.
Let him have them.

00:43:11.360 --> 00:43:12.916
You get all the crabs yourself.

00:43:12.983 --> 00:43:16.161
-Steve, that's a true local,
he doesn't want crab.

00:43:16.228 --> 00:43:18.110
-I eat plenty of it. You enjoy it.

00:43:18.641 --> 00:43:19.524
You enjoy it.

00:43:21.015 --> 00:43:23.133
-You know what?
-Talk to me.

00:43:23.200 --> 00:43:25.375
Let's say a little lunch prayer.

00:43:25.864 --> 00:43:28.968
Just a little one to yourself.
I'm gonna just say it to myself.

00:43:29.035 --> 00:43:31.534
-Okay. You do that every meal, Steve?
-I try to.

00:43:31.601 --> 00:43:33.972
Lord thank you for this meal,

00:43:34.565 --> 00:43:37.109
and for the restaurant,
and thanks for Peter,

00:43:37.986 --> 00:43:39.793
and… amen.

00:43:39.860 --> 00:43:41.188
-Amen.
-That's a short one.

00:43:41.255 --> 00:43:43.218
-Thank you, Steve.
-[Aaron] Chow down.

00:43:43.285 --> 00:43:47.633
My granddaddy's prayer,
Ernest Hamilton, every year he would go,

00:43:47.700 --> 00:43:50.673
"God thank you for this food.
In the name of Jesus, amen."

00:43:50.740 --> 00:43:52.070
Everybody eat.

00:43:52.137 --> 00:43:53.174
So fried?

00:43:53.653 --> 00:43:55.203
-Fried.
-Corn?

00:43:55.271 --> 00:43:59.219
They got flour, cornmeal, corn in it.

00:43:59.692 --> 00:44:02.253
Some people put bell peppers.

00:44:03.167 --> 00:44:06.995
It's a local thing.
Seafood and hush puppies go together.

00:44:07.815 --> 00:44:08.874
They're excellent.

00:44:09.400 --> 00:44:11.096
What do you want to eat?

00:44:11.163 --> 00:44:12.924
-I'm fine.
-You don't want anything?

00:44:12.991 --> 00:44:14.793
-No. Eat your crab.
-Serious?

00:44:16.668 --> 00:44:17.995
Mmm. That's good.

00:44:18.740 --> 00:44:20.596
What's your technique for these guys?

00:44:20.663 --> 00:44:22.878
You just open them up
as much as you can.

00:44:22.945 --> 00:44:24.900
Take it and try to get…

00:44:25.949 --> 00:44:28.067
-As much as possible.
-Yeah this part.

00:44:30.542 --> 00:44:32.038
Then you dip that.

00:44:33.033 --> 00:44:33.916
Yeah.

00:44:33.984 --> 00:44:37.439
And just
because there's a membrane in between it.

00:44:37.506 --> 00:44:41.299
So you bite down until
you feel the membrane then just pull off.

00:44:41.366 --> 00:44:44.910
 And it's… not something
you get excited about anymore?

00:44:45.644 --> 00:44:46.744
Take your time.

00:44:47.445 --> 00:44:49.327
I get them any time I want them.

00:44:50.472 --> 00:44:51.642
I got a…

00:44:51.709 --> 00:44:53.591
-That's good ain't it? Huh?
-Mmm.

00:44:54.302 --> 00:44:56.537
I think it's better without the sauce.

00:44:57.262 --> 00:44:58.215
You like the sauce?

00:44:58.282 --> 00:45:02.551
That's the Everglades… stone crabs.

00:45:02.618 --> 00:45:04.777
The different areas or taste different.

00:45:04.844 --> 00:45:06.703
Here they're better.

00:45:06.770 --> 00:45:07.946
They're just better.

00:45:08.390 --> 00:45:10.630
-It's just a nice thick meat.
-Yep.

00:45:10.697 --> 00:45:11.804
-Sweet.
-Yep.

00:45:12.700 --> 00:45:14.142
Now I'd dip that one.

00:45:14.209 --> 00:45:15.092
Mm-hmm.

00:45:17.774 --> 00:45:19.608
Is it unreal or what?

00:45:19.675 --> 00:45:22.097
That's Everglades stone crab for you.

00:45:22.164 --> 00:45:25.204
Now you go to Tampa or somewhere
and get their stone crab…

00:45:25.271 --> 00:45:26.394
They don't touch it?

00:45:26.461 --> 00:45:28.178
They don't touch our stone crabs.

00:45:28.245 --> 00:45:31.911
They'll argue with you but I'm telling you
we got better stone crabs.

00:45:31.978 --> 00:45:32.861
Mmm.

00:45:34.585 --> 00:45:35.878
Look at these things.

00:45:36.770 --> 00:45:40.311
Did you guys change these flags
or did you kept that as is?

00:45:40.378 --> 00:45:42.757
-No, I put all this stuff up.
-This is all you?

00:45:42.824 --> 00:45:44.885
I make this artwork here, the chandelier.

00:45:44.952 --> 00:45:45.868
-Oh nice!

00:45:45.935 --> 00:45:47.513
-I make bonsai trees.

00:45:47.580 --> 00:45:49.023
-The flag? Who did the flag?

00:45:49.090 --> 00:45:51.905
-There's a guy in Naples.
I told him to give me his name.

00:45:51.972 --> 00:45:54.583
I do not know his name
but he does amazing work.

00:45:54.650 --> 00:45:56.383
The boats are my uncle's.

00:45:56.450 --> 00:45:57.788
He just passed away.

00:45:57.855 --> 00:46:00.180
My aunt were married 81 years.

00:46:00.247 --> 00:46:01.130
-Oh wow.

00:46:01.197 --> 00:46:03.423
And then she passed away a month before.

00:46:03.490 --> 00:46:05.711
-Your aunt?
-She just passed away, yeah.

00:46:06.824 --> 00:46:08.169
How old was she?

00:46:08.236 --> 00:46:10.068
94.

00:46:10.568 --> 00:46:14.783
And he was 96. So yeah,
they had a wonderful life together.

00:46:14.850 --> 00:46:16.149
Are you a regular here?

00:46:16.216 --> 00:46:19.173
This is the Manzini's better half.

00:46:19.240 --> 00:46:21.043
I follow Manzie. That's my guy.

00:46:21.110 --> 00:46:22.444
Three years dating him.

00:46:22.511 --> 00:46:24.687
Oh the musician. So you're a groupie?

00:46:25.273 --> 00:46:26.184
Hi y'all.

00:46:26.251 --> 00:46:27.820
Kind of like equipment manager.

00:46:27.887 --> 00:46:29.837
-How long you been with him?
-Excuse me.

00:46:29.904 --> 00:46:31.323
-Three years.
-Three years?

00:46:31.390 --> 00:46:32.553
-I'm 80.

00:46:32.621 --> 00:46:33.832
-You're 80?
-Yes.

00:46:33.899 --> 00:46:35.168
-No you're not.
-Yes I am.

00:46:35.235 --> 00:46:37.218
-Okay.
-I'm 80. He's 79.

00:46:38.195 --> 00:46:40.061
And it's just new life.

00:46:40.128 --> 00:46:41.903
I know. We're both widowed.

00:46:41.970 --> 00:46:43.088
You've gotta smile.

00:46:43.729 --> 00:46:44.612
That's the key.

00:46:45.364 --> 00:46:48.117
And be happy for what you have.

00:46:48.204 --> 00:46:49.498
And don't always want.

00:46:50.209 --> 00:46:52.485
Amen. Amen.

00:46:53.480 --> 00:46:54.598
He wrote this song.

00:46:55.130 --> 00:46:56.550
He wrote this.

00:46:56.617 --> 00:46:58.088
-He wrote this one?
-Yeah.

00:46:58.155 --> 00:46:59.038
[Manzie plays]

00:47:05.481 --> 00:47:06.561
[Peter] Oh wow.

00:47:06.628 --> 00:47:08.899
Aaron, you're going full. That's crazy.

00:47:08.966 --> 00:47:10.062
Cook it myself.

00:47:10.535 --> 00:47:12.023
-That's crazy.
-You all right?

00:47:12.090 --> 00:47:14.718
Yeah but that's crazy.
I don't want all that.

00:47:14.785 --> 00:47:16.091
No this is yours.

00:47:17.219 --> 00:47:18.386
There we go.

00:47:18.453 --> 00:47:21.312
Got our world famous peel and eat shrimp.

00:47:21.379 --> 00:47:23.850
-Oh nice.
-Our world famous Cuban sandwich.

00:47:24.340 --> 00:47:25.902
We got our grilled shrimp.

00:47:26.680 --> 00:47:28.152
Blackened shrimp.

00:47:28.219 --> 00:47:30.089
You know what you ought to let me do?

00:47:30.156 --> 00:47:33.048
Is bring you in bay leaves from the swamp.

00:47:33.595 --> 00:47:35.380
-I got bay leaves.
-Absolutely.

00:47:35.447 --> 00:47:36.683
-I'll bring them in.

00:47:37.250 --> 00:47:39.019
[Peter] So what are you doing here?

00:47:39.086 --> 00:47:41.514
Just straight up shrimp,
beans, rice, plantains?

00:47:41.581 --> 00:47:43.934
Yeah, I told him that I like the shrimp.

00:47:45.010 --> 00:47:48.108
And the rice and look what he made me.

00:47:48.628 --> 00:47:51.283
-Oh that's what you want.
-I'll never eat it.

00:47:51.350 --> 00:47:53.232
I can't. No way to eat all that.

00:47:54.220 --> 00:47:56.177
That's one thing I can say about

00:47:56.244 --> 00:47:58.404
is they just give so much.

00:47:59.114 --> 00:48:00.283
Yeah, portions are big.

00:48:00.350 --> 00:48:01.943
Portions are giant.

00:48:02.010 --> 00:48:03.363
Wait till you taste it.

00:48:03.957 --> 00:48:05.883
Yeah. Nice jumbo shrimp.

00:48:05.950 --> 00:48:08.128
These aren't local though are they?

00:48:08.195 --> 00:48:09.389
I don't know.

00:48:09.470 --> 00:48:12.176
-No we don't have shrimpers around here.
-Okay.

00:48:13.693 --> 00:48:14.576
Mmm.

00:48:15.560 --> 00:48:17.207
Is that unreal or what?

00:48:17.274 --> 00:48:18.888
What's his partner's name?

00:48:18.955 --> 00:48:20.267
David.

00:48:20.348 --> 00:48:22.876
 So good. Oh you cooked this, Aaron?

00:48:22.943 --> 00:48:24.555
-I cooked it today.
-Nice, Aaron.

00:48:24.622 --> 00:48:27.795
-Where do you get the shrimp from?
-They are from the Gulf.

00:48:27.862 --> 00:48:29.194
They are from the Gulf.

00:48:29.261 --> 00:48:32.483
Our snapper is from the Gulf.
Our stone crabs are from the Gulf.

00:48:32.550 --> 00:48:35.856
We do sell mahi-mahi
but I believe that comes from the Atlantic.

00:48:36.190 --> 00:48:38.596
-Yeah.
-You went too far. This is unreal.

00:48:39.317 --> 00:48:40.258
Oh, yeah.

00:48:40.333 --> 00:48:43.952
Well you know we've gotta show y'all
what we can do here at Havana Cafe.

00:48:44.019 --> 00:48:46.263
So my wife has to edit these videos.

00:48:46.330 --> 00:48:48.933
She'll be watching the food
sitting at home.

00:48:49.640 --> 00:48:53.302
And then that night she's like
we gotta go get the closest thing to that.

00:48:53.389 --> 00:48:56.163
-I'll bring her down sometime.
-We can put you in the motel.

00:48:56.230 --> 00:48:57.261
You do amazing work.

00:48:57.328 --> 00:48:59.219
They got a clean motel.

00:48:59.286 --> 00:49:01.307
-Ain't never been underwater.
-Yeah.

00:49:02.100 --> 00:49:03.866
-That's a big deal.
-Yeah, big deal.

00:49:03.933 --> 00:49:07.089
Never been… So many motels around here.

00:49:07.156 --> 00:49:09.651
-They've been under?
-And they never do nothing.

00:49:10.628 --> 00:49:12.811
It's moldy. You can smell it.

00:49:13.420 --> 00:49:15.832
I always send everybody to his place.

00:49:16.399 --> 00:49:19.208
-What's your place called?
-Parkway Motel and Marina.

00:49:19.275 --> 00:49:20.803
Parkway Motel and Marina.

00:49:21.295 --> 00:49:24.033
You do this?
You also have a bar in Fort Lauderdale?

00:49:24.100 --> 00:49:26.048
Yeah. Thank God it runs itself.

00:49:26.115 --> 00:49:28.949
I'm gonna have to take the Cuban to go.

00:49:29.016 --> 00:49:29.927
I'll take a bite.

00:49:29.994 --> 00:49:32.893
-You gotta dunk it
into the sauce of the shrimp.

00:49:32.960 --> 00:49:35.725
-Take a bite first, you get a real taste.
-Okay.

00:49:38.204 --> 00:49:40.304
-Have you ever ate a Cuban before?
-Mm-hmm.

00:49:40.371 --> 00:49:41.254
So yeah we're…

00:49:42.325 --> 00:49:44.338
-And then dip.
-Dip it. Oh my God yes.

00:49:44.405 --> 00:49:45.462
You got to go…

00:49:45.529 --> 00:49:48.006
-With the garlic and all the good stuff.

00:49:48.073 --> 00:49:49.623
What's in the sauce here?

00:49:49.690 --> 00:49:52.071
Salted butter, minced garlic,

00:49:52.604 --> 00:49:55.961
a little bit of Old Bay,
and then we put our hot sauce in.

00:49:56.028 --> 00:49:59.598
They got a killer hot sauce.
I forgot about their hot sauce.

00:49:59.665 --> 00:50:01.190
This is fire.

00:50:01.847 --> 00:50:04.012
This is better than any food I had in Cuba.

00:50:04.079 --> 00:50:05.268
[Aaron chuckles]

00:50:05.335 --> 00:50:07.767
You got the Rod and Gun Club you can go to.

00:50:07.834 --> 00:50:09.703
You can go to River Wilderness.

00:50:09.770 --> 00:50:12.121
River Wilderness has never been underwater.

00:50:12.188 --> 00:50:13.966
River Wilderness. Yeah.

00:50:14.033 --> 00:50:15.813
-And they're local.
-Yeah.

00:50:15.880 --> 00:50:18.806
All the other ones have been
bought up by big corporations.

00:50:18.873 --> 00:50:20.553
-Corporations.
-They've come here?

00:50:20.620 --> 00:50:21.582
The guy from India.

00:50:21.649 --> 00:50:23.923
-Hashish family.
-Hashish. Everything.

00:50:23.990 --> 00:50:26.509
Key West all the way up the East Coast.

00:50:26.576 --> 00:50:28.782
They own… Who's this family?

00:50:29.636 --> 00:50:31.459
-Patels.
-Patels.

00:50:31.526 --> 00:50:35.796
You know that's the name of almost
any Indian that's got money is a Patel.

00:50:35.863 --> 00:50:39.696
I mean they're real nice people
but to come into a small town and buy…

00:50:39.763 --> 00:50:41.463
-They've taken over.
-Restaurants.

00:50:41.530 --> 00:50:44.038
Put you out of business
and then buy your business.

00:50:44.105 --> 00:50:45.461
-Yeah.
-That's what they do.

00:50:45.528 --> 00:50:48.202
One small airboat tour is left.

00:50:48.269 --> 00:50:49.943
-That's it.
-In Everglades City.

00:50:50.010 --> 00:50:51.161
All of them.

00:50:51.228 --> 00:50:52.922
-Are you serious?
-All of them.

00:50:52.989 --> 00:50:54.873
Except one in Everglades City.

00:50:54.940 --> 00:50:56.413
Captain Doug.

00:50:56.480 --> 00:50:58.660
Original Everglades Airboat.

00:50:58.727 --> 00:51:00.223
And you've got Corey Billie's

00:51:00.290 --> 00:51:01.736
That's the local and you got…

00:51:01.803 --> 00:51:04.952
-So how did they manage…
So listen. I'm gonna tell you.

00:51:05.391 --> 00:51:06.528
I'm gonna tell you.

00:51:06.595 --> 00:51:09.015
They come into town and made friends.

00:51:09.488 --> 00:51:11.620
They bought a little airboat tour.

00:51:11.687 --> 00:51:13.734
They started two-for-one tickets.

00:51:14.294 --> 00:51:16.587
So all these little companies

00:51:16.654 --> 00:51:20.503
like Speedy's and them
they can't go two-for-one.

00:51:20.570 --> 00:51:22.955
They take four people,
two of them's free.

00:51:23.371 --> 00:51:28.161
They make $90 off of a ticket
and they put them out of business.

00:51:28.228 --> 00:51:30.398
So then they buy them. Buy them out.

00:51:30.465 --> 00:51:35.273
So they advertise
ride on Jungler's ride on Speedy's.

00:51:35.340 --> 00:51:39.193
So you think you're riding
on a different… it's all the same.

00:51:39.260 --> 00:51:42.441
There's that friction with big money
from the outside coming in.

00:51:42.508 --> 00:51:45.363
Oh they bought the motels.
They bought everything.

00:51:46.000 --> 00:51:48.543
The only motels are, you got Kenny's.

00:51:48.610 --> 00:51:50.143
River Wilderness.

00:51:50.210 --> 00:51:52.003
-Rod and Gun Club.
-Yup.

00:51:52.070 --> 00:51:53.596
And I think that's it right?

00:51:53.663 --> 00:51:55.930
He owns Everglades City Motel.

00:51:55.997 --> 00:51:58.987
-Ivy House.
-He owns the Ivy House.

00:51:59.054 --> 00:52:02.541
He owns the Everglades Motel.

00:52:02.608 --> 00:52:04.807
Then he owns the Captain's Table.

00:52:05.541 --> 00:52:09.283
And then he's trying to buy the old
Restaurant Depot and to tear that down

00:52:09.350 --> 00:52:12.593
which is the train station
that was built a long time ago.

00:52:12.660 --> 00:52:16.479
And because he's got so much money
he's the Everglades City…

00:52:16.546 --> 00:52:19.566
The Everglades National Park
Boat Tours he's got.

00:52:20.075 --> 00:52:22.223
Took the boat tours. He owns it all.

00:52:22.963 --> 00:52:26.094
Okay so if a big corporation
buys something like here,

00:52:26.168 --> 00:52:28.053
it's not for sale by the way, right?

00:52:28.120 --> 00:52:29.851
Absolutely not to him. [laughs]

00:52:29.918 --> 00:52:34.105
Okay. But then the food quality
is gonna take a turn south really quick.

00:52:34.172 --> 00:52:36.001
Just like the airboat tour business.

00:52:36.068 --> 00:52:38.751
Yeah we're lucky that he does not do food.

00:52:38.818 --> 00:52:40.617
-Okay.
-Because food is you know…

00:52:40.684 --> 00:52:42.538
I'm just saying not him, but anyone.

00:52:42.605 --> 00:52:45.061
They come in,
they're trying to maximize profits.

00:52:45.128 --> 00:52:46.034
Yeah.

00:52:46.101 --> 00:52:47.943
-It's not about the community.

00:52:48.010 --> 00:52:50.276
-Correct.
-Your face isn't here every day.

00:52:50.662 --> 00:52:52.741
You don't care.
You just wanna make money.

00:52:52.808 --> 00:52:55.373
-I love my employees.
-And then the soul of it goes.

00:52:55.440 --> 00:52:56.381
He loves locals.

00:52:57.105 --> 00:53:00.888
He lives right across the road from me.
We holler out at each other.

00:53:00.955 --> 00:53:02.873
Chokoloskee's 4th of July,

00:53:03.631 --> 00:53:05.724
They put on the… And New Year's,

00:53:05.791 --> 00:53:08.116
they put on the biggest show.

00:53:08.183 --> 00:53:10.366
Bigger than the fireworks in Everglades.

00:53:10.433 --> 00:53:12.573
They do, out of their pocket.

00:53:12.640 --> 00:53:14.669
-Nice.
-I love fireworks. What can I say?

00:53:14.736 --> 00:53:17.463
They fire off. It's unbelievable.

00:53:17.530 --> 00:53:21.177
Boom boom boom.
Some unreal fireworks. I love it.

00:53:25.500 --> 00:53:26.853
[Peter] Take care, bye.

00:53:27.511 --> 00:53:31.403
This is another one of my trees
I made out of aluminum wire.

00:53:31.840 --> 00:53:33.661
-Oh nice. So you're an artist.

00:53:33.728 --> 00:53:34.631
-Yeah.

00:53:34.698 --> 00:53:37.413
-That's cool. Are you selling this stuff?
-Yeah, yeah.

00:53:37.480 --> 00:53:38.600
[man] Hey, I saw you.

00:53:38.667 --> 00:53:39.550
[Peter] Okay.

00:53:39.617 --> 00:53:43.163
Yeah, yeah.
I just took Captain Steve's buggy tour.

00:53:43.230 --> 00:53:46.333
Yeah, we're with Steve right now.
You want to see Steve again?

00:53:46.400 --> 00:53:48.513
Steve and I are making a video today.

00:53:48.580 --> 00:53:51.363
Yeah we had his cousin driving
I think it was.

00:53:51.430 --> 00:53:52.313
Oh okay.

00:53:52.380 --> 00:53:54.143
Yeah.
That's why we even called him.

00:53:54.210 --> 00:53:56.710
-This is the real, the original.
-This is the real?

00:53:56.777 --> 00:53:57.839
This is the real one.

00:53:57.906 --> 00:54:01.003
-How are you folks doing?
-That other guy was a character too.

00:54:03.040 --> 00:54:07.113
That was… oh I… we're doing…
I went out in the boat today.

00:54:07.180 --> 00:54:09.096
-Oh you guys went with Cheryl.
-Yeah.

00:54:09.163 --> 00:54:10.891
-How'd you like him?
-He was great.

00:54:10.958 --> 00:54:12.269
-He's my cousin.
-Yeah.

00:54:12.336 --> 00:54:13.944
He got a bad review. I can't…

00:54:14.011 --> 00:54:15.883
Yeah yeah. He was all bummed out.

00:54:15.950 --> 00:54:19.834
Yeah we're bummed out
'cause he gets such good reviews.

00:54:19.901 --> 00:54:21.829
No we loved him. He was very personal.

00:54:21.896 --> 00:54:24.686
Would you go on there
and maybe leave a review for us?

00:54:24.753 --> 00:54:25.770
We definitely will.

00:54:25.837 --> 00:54:27.643
Well I appreciate it. Thank you.

00:54:27.710 --> 00:54:29.876
-You're welcome.
-It was nice meeting y'all.

00:54:29.943 --> 00:54:30.926
All the best.

00:54:30.993 --> 00:54:33.526
We watched the one on Citrus…

00:54:33.593 --> 00:54:36.223
-You were up in…
-Immokalee? Apalachia?

00:54:36.290 --> 00:54:37.643
-Yes.
-Yes.

00:54:38.086 --> 00:54:40.923
We're staying in Citrus Springs
because of that too.

00:54:40.990 --> 00:54:42.389
Oh nice. Cool.

00:54:42.456 --> 00:54:46.683
-Hey we appreciate your business.
-Thanks for watching. Appreciate it.

00:54:46.750 --> 00:54:48.515
[music from the bar fades out]

00:54:52.490 --> 00:54:55.199
[Steve] This guy
flying this Confederate flag,

00:54:55.266 --> 00:54:57.174
he cares to give them to people.

00:54:57.241 --> 00:54:58.487
He's from New York.

00:54:58.554 --> 00:54:59.437
-No way.

00:54:59.505 --> 00:55:01.416
-Oh he's straight New Yorker.

00:55:01.483 --> 00:55:04.763
Talks like a New Yorker
but he can't stand New Yorkers.

00:55:05.270 --> 00:55:06.388
Southerner at heart.

00:55:07.773 --> 00:55:09.473
I guess is what you'd say.

00:55:09.540 --> 00:55:12.394
-What is a Southerner at heart?
How would you explain that?

00:55:12.461 --> 00:55:15.584
A southerner at heart
is where you love things

00:55:15.651 --> 00:55:18.074
that are old school and Southern

00:55:18.762 --> 00:55:20.636
cook out of iron skillet

00:55:20.703 --> 00:55:22.953
you know how to make a fire.

00:55:23.020 --> 00:55:25.529
It's not just the way you talk.

00:55:26.249 --> 00:55:28.923
It's that in your heart you love the South.

00:55:28.990 --> 00:55:30.837
You don't get in people's business.

00:55:31.350 --> 00:55:34.046
You don't pay attention
to what other people do.

00:55:34.113 --> 00:55:38.403
And you're fixing to find out
how a real person is right now.

00:55:38.470 --> 00:55:40.422
The Daniel's Compound,

00:55:40.489 --> 00:55:43.474
this old man
is the best thing in the world.

00:55:43.541 --> 00:55:44.870
I love him like a dad.

00:55:45.516 --> 00:55:46.913
So let's go get him.

00:55:48.326 --> 00:55:49.209
[Steve] Daryl!

00:55:49.648 --> 00:55:50.589
[knocks on door]

00:55:51.380 --> 00:55:52.723
He ain't here.

00:55:52.790 --> 00:55:56.055
Car's here. His golf cart's here.

00:55:56.122 --> 00:55:58.122
[Peter] "Beware of attack father."

00:55:59.190 --> 00:56:00.709
Hey where's Daryl at?

00:56:00.776 --> 00:56:02.163
[man] Boat ride.

00:56:02.230 --> 00:56:04.847
-That's Daryl's brother.
-Let's go talk to him.

00:56:04.914 --> 00:56:07.770
Come on! Let's sit down on the porch.

00:56:08.280 --> 00:56:10.633
Sit down. Somebody wants to talk to ya.

00:56:11.265 --> 00:56:12.903
-We got storm clouds coming in.

00:56:12.970 --> 00:56:14.522
That ain't gonna bother nobody.

00:56:14.589 --> 00:56:17.754
In Florida they say the more south
you go the more north it gets

00:56:17.821 --> 00:56:20.518
until you get really south.
Then it gets really South.

00:56:20.585 --> 00:56:24.259
We're about south as far as you can go,
unless you go to Key West.

00:56:24.326 --> 00:56:27.648
-How you doing sir?
-This is Cheryl Daniels.

00:56:27.715 --> 00:56:29.526
-This is Peter.
-Peter how you doing?

00:56:29.593 --> 00:56:32.001
I'm making a video of your friend today.

00:56:32.068 --> 00:56:33.938
-Oh okay.
-Yeah we're getting into it.

00:56:34.005 --> 00:56:36.381
-Well you coulda' done worse.
-[Steve chuckles]

00:56:36.448 --> 00:56:39.381
-Coulda' done better.
-Am I doing better that you're in it?

00:56:39.448 --> 00:56:40.908
-Them people loved you.
-Huh?

00:56:40.975 --> 00:56:44.713
Them people I talked to them
that rode in the tour. They loved you.

00:56:44.780 --> 00:56:47.691
They all loved me
as long as I don't talk about myself.

00:56:47.758 --> 00:56:49.051
I got a bad review.

00:56:49.610 --> 00:56:51.919
I heard about that.
That really bummed you out.

00:56:51.986 --> 00:56:52.898
Yes it did.

00:56:52.965 --> 00:56:54.044
Don't worry about it.

00:56:54.111 --> 00:56:57.185
You're gonna get some people
that are unhappy with everything.

00:56:57.252 --> 00:56:59.935
I understand that
but you don't understand me.

00:57:00.002 --> 00:57:03.739
I go out of my way on them boat rides.
You know what I mean?

00:57:04.241 --> 00:57:07.923
Let me get your mic off.
Do you mind if I put this on your pocket?

00:57:07.990 --> 00:57:10.045
Yeah it's recording whatcha gonna ask me.

00:57:10.112 --> 00:57:12.867
Whatever you want to say.
I don't really have any plans.

00:57:12.934 --> 00:57:14.986
I just try to learn from the locals.

00:57:15.053 --> 00:57:16.219
Yeah I gotcha.

00:57:16.286 --> 00:57:19.180
Well most people,
first thing they want to talk about

00:57:19.247 --> 00:57:21.653
is hauling marijuana back in the day.

00:57:21.720 --> 00:57:23.235
-We already talked about that.

00:57:23.302 --> 00:57:26.712
Yeah and I don't get into that.
You know what I mean?

00:57:26.779 --> 00:57:29.450
I know what I did was wrong
but I'm not ashamed of it.

00:57:29.517 --> 00:57:31.844
-You understand what I'm saying?
-I understand.

00:57:31.911 --> 00:57:35.019
And I spent 25 years
in prison because of it.

00:57:35.086 --> 00:57:37.582
Eight one time in Eglin.

00:57:37.649 --> 00:57:39.220
Steve was in there with me

00:57:39.287 --> 00:57:42.921
and I said I don't want to talk about it.
Listen to me.

00:57:42.988 --> 00:57:45.547
-Yeah you don't want to
and you're talking about it.

00:57:45.614 --> 00:57:47.944
But now that you're talking about it,
25 years…

00:57:48.016 --> 00:57:49.835
I don't like to get into detail.

00:57:49.902 --> 00:57:52.848
I don't like naming names.
I don't like doing that.

00:57:52.915 --> 00:57:53.945
I went back in

00:57:54.491 --> 00:57:58.680
and I got turned in
for killing deer out of season.

00:57:58.747 --> 00:58:00.173
-Killing deer out of season?

00:58:00.240 --> 00:58:03.951
Yeah and a very good friend of mine
was with me. At least I thought he was.

00:58:04.018 --> 00:58:06.499
He wanted to kill the deer
but he couldn't hit him

00:58:06.566 --> 00:58:08.530
so I took the rifle and I shot him.

00:58:08.596 --> 00:58:12.740
And he told the game wardens
that he felt it was his duty.

00:58:13.404 --> 00:58:16.468
-So you went to prison for killing a deer?
-Then I went back in.

00:58:16.535 --> 00:58:19.213
The last time I went,
I went 17 and a half years.

00:58:19.280 --> 00:58:21.213
-What was that for?
-Marijuana.

00:58:21.280 --> 00:58:23.870
What would you say Steve?
Was it marijuana?

00:58:23.937 --> 00:58:26.349
Or they said it was cocaine
but it wasn't.

00:58:27.250 --> 00:58:31.803
Okay. So as Steve said
federal prison is like Boy Scout camp.

00:58:31.870 --> 00:58:34.013
-Would you say that?
-Saved my life.

00:58:34.080 --> 00:58:35.931
-Saved your life? How?
-Saved my life.

00:58:35.998 --> 00:58:38.475
Because I'm a man of God now.

00:58:38.542 --> 00:58:40.215
And I got that in there mostly.

00:58:40.935 --> 00:58:44.834
And I read the Bible so many times
I don't even tell people.

00:58:44.901 --> 00:58:46.973
-I was talking about Eglin.

00:58:47.040 --> 00:58:50.803
Oh yeah Eglin was…
Eglin was a good place to get in trouble.

00:58:51.303 --> 00:58:52.635
That's what I told him.

00:58:52.702 --> 00:58:54.583
It was a good place to get in trouble

00:58:54.650 --> 00:58:56.188
because we had money.

00:58:57.138 --> 00:59:00.898
And when we had money our girlfriends
lived right down the road.

00:59:00.965 --> 00:59:03.457
The people that we worked for on the base

00:59:03.524 --> 00:59:04.910
he ratted me out too.

00:59:04.977 --> 00:59:07.061
And we'd pay him $50 a day.

00:59:07.128 --> 00:59:09.048
He'd drop us off with our girlfriends.

00:59:09.115 --> 00:59:11.790
He'd pick us back up
at the end of the day.

00:59:12.372 --> 00:59:13.650
So we had it made.

00:59:14.195 --> 00:59:17.947
And it was all a game in prison.

00:59:18.014 --> 00:59:19.189
It was a game.

00:59:19.256 --> 00:59:22.699
I never ever…
and I'll tell you this flat out right now

00:59:22.766 --> 00:59:25.295
I never did a hard day
in prison in my life.

00:59:26.373 --> 00:59:27.483
25 years?

00:59:27.550 --> 00:59:28.781
Never had a hard day.

00:59:29.244 --> 00:59:30.306
'Cause I accepted it.

00:59:30.373 --> 00:59:32.629
-Hardest part was
being away from your family.

00:59:32.696 --> 00:59:33.669
Well that's normal.

00:59:33.735 --> 00:59:36.171
But no, I never had a hard day of prison.

00:59:36.238 --> 00:59:37.993
The wardens weren't hard on you?

00:59:38.060 --> 00:59:39.909
Every one of them liked me.

00:59:39.976 --> 00:59:40.963
-You were buddies?

00:59:41.030 --> 00:59:42.483
'Cause I was a standup man.

00:59:42.883 --> 00:59:46.056
The people that I worked for
and I ain't giving no names on that

00:59:46.123 --> 00:59:47.280
they turned me in.

00:59:47.347 --> 00:59:49.133
The kingpin, he turned me in.

00:59:49.599 --> 00:59:54.243
When I went to court they started asking me
about this and that and nothing.

00:59:54.310 --> 00:59:56.797
And I told him
I says I'm not gonna rat.

00:59:56.876 --> 01:00:00.331
He said well if you just give us
these boys' names that turnt you in.

01:00:00.398 --> 01:00:02.803
Your bosses. He says you won't do a day.

01:00:03.271 --> 01:00:04.502
Steve was in court…

01:00:04.569 --> 01:00:05.913
-You weren't gonna snitch?

01:00:05.980 --> 01:00:08.170
I wouldn't snitch on nobody.

01:00:08.237 --> 01:00:10.706
There ain't nobody made me do anything.

01:00:10.773 --> 01:00:12.304
I knew right what I was doing.

01:00:12.371 --> 01:00:14.981
Nobody held a gun to my head
and said do it.

01:00:15.048 --> 01:00:17.217
So I'm gonna go
put somebody else in prison,

01:00:17.284 --> 01:00:19.904
ruin their life
because it's something I didn't know.

01:00:19.971 --> 01:00:21.585
-You know it's a familiar story.

01:00:21.652 --> 01:00:24.919
I did a story with a guy
out in Humboldt County, California.

01:00:24.986 --> 01:00:27.786
A lot of marijuana
comes from that part of the country.

01:00:27.853 --> 01:00:30.281
And they offered the same thing.

01:00:30.348 --> 01:00:32.054
They said, if you snitch

01:00:32.586 --> 01:00:35.766
you don't have to go in and he had a wife.

01:00:35.833 --> 01:00:36.940
He wouldn't snitch.

01:00:37.007 --> 01:00:40.610
The kingpins that I worked for,
the number one man,

01:00:41.041 --> 01:00:44.633
they brought it, and they got it,
and hired me to bring it in.

01:00:44.700 --> 01:00:46.137
They snitched on me.

01:00:46.847 --> 01:00:50.111
And by doing that now
they did seven years.

01:00:50.937 --> 01:00:53.313
I did 17 and a half.

01:00:53.380 --> 01:00:56.949
We lived the life of Riley here
if you will didn't we Steve?

01:00:57.016 --> 01:00:58.438
We had this island.

01:00:58.505 --> 01:01:01.177
But when we was young and we were kids

01:01:01.244 --> 01:01:05.346
we didn't have to have chaperones
watching us as we went around the island.

01:01:05.413 --> 01:01:08.620
We'd be out there on the edge
of them islands with mangrove trees

01:01:08.687 --> 01:01:12.595
with an oar or a stick in our hand
gigging fish having a good time.

01:01:12.662 --> 01:01:16.016
Everybody watched out
for everybody else's kids.

01:01:16.083 --> 01:01:19.643
-If we got hungry, you stopped in…
-First house we come to.

01:01:19.710 --> 01:01:21.913
-There's Darrell.
-Darrell!

01:01:21.980 --> 01:01:23.991
-He don't mind talking.
-I appreciate it.

01:01:24.058 --> 01:01:25.978
I feel uncomfortable talking about it.

01:01:26.045 --> 01:01:27.253
You're great.

01:01:27.320 --> 01:01:29.583
-Thank you Cheryl.
-Thank you Cheryl.

01:01:29.650 --> 01:01:31.618
Don't give me a bad report now.

01:01:31.685 --> 01:01:32.568
[chuckles]

01:01:35.170 --> 01:01:36.946
I'll give you a call after a while.

01:01:37.720 --> 01:01:39.671
-I love you.
-I love you too, son.

01:01:40.190 --> 01:01:42.495
My grandkid,
he's doing something I'm proud of.

01:01:42.562 --> 01:01:43.530
He got out of here.

01:01:43.597 --> 01:01:47.753
He went to North Carolina
and trained for the power companies.

01:01:47.820 --> 01:01:49.293
A lineman. He's a lineman.

01:01:49.360 --> 01:01:50.673
He's my great-grandson.

01:01:50.740 --> 01:01:54.813
I'm glad he had enough to step out,
get out of here. You know what I mean?

01:01:54.880 --> 01:01:56.389
There's nothing here for him.

01:01:56.456 --> 01:01:59.033
-So you would want
the young generation to get out?

01:01:59.100 --> 01:02:00.565
Let's just put it like this,

01:02:00.632 --> 01:02:03.043
the only thing here is to run airboats

01:02:03.110 --> 01:02:05.970
and we don't know
how much longer that'll last.

01:02:06.037 --> 01:02:06.920
You understand?

01:02:08.020 --> 01:02:09.655
-How's this?
-That's great.

01:02:10.178 --> 01:02:12.973
My daddy and mother,
have you told them about Fakahatchee?

01:02:13.040 --> 01:02:13.933
-Nope.

01:02:14.000 --> 01:02:17.933
There's an island up this way about
eight miles called Fakahatchee Island.

01:02:18.000 --> 01:02:20.102
My family homesteaded that island.

01:02:20.169 --> 01:02:22.963
It's a 60-acre island
that the Indians made.

01:02:23.030 --> 01:02:25.981
Now the government in the middle '60s

01:02:26.048 --> 01:02:28.913
decided they gon' move
everybody off of all the islands.

01:02:28.980 --> 01:02:31.358
So they moved my family off of the island.

01:02:31.870 --> 01:02:36.483
Before that a hurricane come through
and tore the schoolhouse up down there.

01:02:36.550 --> 01:02:39.776
So my daddy and mother
had my oldest brother at that time.

01:02:39.843 --> 01:02:42.886
So they moved in here
to put the boy in school.

01:02:42.953 --> 01:02:45.906
Then I was born on the island
after they got here.

01:02:45.973 --> 01:02:48.770
But whenever they come here,
soon as they got down here,

01:02:48.837 --> 01:02:50.906
they bought this acre of land right here.

01:02:50.973 --> 01:02:53.184
Had two livable homes on it

01:02:53.251 --> 01:02:55.286
and me and my brother still own it.

01:02:55.353 --> 01:02:57.481
I've lived right here all my life.

01:02:57.548 --> 01:02:59.433
I've never lived anywhere else.

01:02:59.500 --> 01:03:03.504
I was in the construction business
for quite a few years back in

01:03:03.571 --> 01:03:06.030
about '79,
somewhere in that area.

01:03:06.097 --> 01:03:07.789
-Okay.
-So I built my home then.

01:03:08.290 --> 01:03:10.911
But we grew up as commercial fishermens

01:03:10.978 --> 01:03:13.203
till I was about in my 40s.

01:03:13.270 --> 01:03:14.877
Then that's when the government…

01:03:14.944 --> 01:03:18.716
When the government
made us all move off of all the islands.

01:03:18.783 --> 01:03:22.963
They also stopped our way of living.
They said your commercial fishing is over.

01:03:23.030 --> 01:03:26.195
You got to go find another way
to make a living and we did.

01:03:26.262 --> 01:03:29.154
And money-wise

01:03:29.221 --> 01:03:31.623
it probably didn't hurt us any at all.

01:03:31.690 --> 01:03:35.392
But I look at fishing like a lot of people.

01:03:35.950 --> 01:03:38.126
Like I think farmers look at farming.

01:03:39.030 --> 01:03:41.206
-It's in their blood. You understand?
-Yeah.

01:03:41.273 --> 01:03:44.766
A lot of the boys here
when they stopped us from fishing

01:03:44.833 --> 01:03:46.874
a lot of them didn't know nothing else.

01:03:46.941 --> 01:03:49.263
I did. I owned a big boat.

01:03:49.330 --> 01:03:51.578
I stone crabbed for 23 years

01:03:51.645 --> 01:03:54.537
and the construction business.

01:03:55.457 --> 01:03:57.413
I was a workaholic all my life.

01:03:57.480 --> 01:03:59.305
I mean I worked.

01:03:59.685 --> 01:04:00.586
[Steve] Still is.

01:04:00.653 --> 01:04:02.543
And I still do it.

01:04:02.610 --> 01:04:04.172
It's just my way of life.

01:04:04.239 --> 01:04:06.045
But no, I've lived a good life here.

01:04:06.112 --> 01:04:07.813
It was a good place to grow up.

01:04:07.880 --> 01:04:09.457
I was born in '42.

01:04:09.524 --> 01:04:11.050
-Okay. Good for you.

01:04:11.117 --> 01:04:15.093
The only thing that changed
was what we could do you know.

01:04:15.160 --> 01:04:17.009
We were…

01:04:17.483 --> 01:04:20.533
and I'm talking all of us boys,
Steve, all of us.

01:04:20.600 --> 01:04:21.483
We were sort of

01:04:22.232 --> 01:04:23.742
we weren't a wild bunch.

01:04:23.809 --> 01:04:25.686
But we liked to hunt a lot

01:04:26.239 --> 01:04:27.122
and

01:04:27.975 --> 01:04:29.860
drink a lot. We drank a lot.

01:04:30.333 --> 01:04:31.274
[Peter chuckles]

01:04:31.830 --> 01:04:33.093
But life's changed.

01:04:33.160 --> 01:04:36.656
I hadn't had a drink in, what,
30 years or something like that.

01:04:36.723 --> 01:04:37.937
When my son died

01:04:38.570 --> 01:04:40.687
I had a 50-foot boat and I was out of town.

01:04:40.754 --> 01:04:43.944
He called me wanting to go fishing
with three other boys.

01:04:44.011 --> 01:04:46.944
And they borrowed my boat
and went out into the Gulf.

01:04:47.011 --> 01:04:49.889
That was 30 years ago
and we've never heard of them again.

01:04:49.956 --> 01:04:50.861
So…

01:04:50.928 --> 01:04:52.912
-Nobody knows what happened?
-Nobody.

01:04:52.979 --> 01:04:55.629
It was the biggest search
that ever went on down here.

01:04:55.696 --> 01:04:57.382
-Nothing?
-We never found nothing.

01:04:57.449 --> 01:05:00.162
-Just like they disappeared.
-Did they go out at night?

01:05:00.229 --> 01:05:03.820
Yeah it was night and it was blowing
that weekend that they went.

01:05:03.887 --> 01:05:06.534
So nobody really knows what happened.
It just…

01:05:07.320 --> 01:05:08.351
But…

01:05:09.480 --> 01:05:11.195
it's hard when you lose people.

01:05:11.262 --> 01:05:16.085
But think of the thousands and thousands
and thousands that's losing kids today.

01:05:16.152 --> 01:05:17.089
You know?

01:05:17.156 --> 01:05:20.136
So the world is full of heartache.

01:05:20.203 --> 01:05:21.615
We have to live with it.

01:05:23.586 --> 01:05:24.994
And one thing

01:05:26.009 --> 01:05:27.262
when I was young

01:05:29.216 --> 01:05:30.109
I said, you know,

01:05:31.427 --> 01:05:33.693
I can't let life stop me from living.

01:05:34.190 --> 01:05:36.166
So I sort of set myself up

01:05:37.572 --> 01:05:39.408
not to get hurt.
Do you understand?

01:05:39.475 --> 01:05:42.593
And no matter what happened to me
I had to keep going.

01:05:43.450 --> 01:05:46.228
And I did.
So it's sort of harden your heart.

01:05:46.295 --> 01:05:47.758
Do you understand?

01:05:47.825 --> 01:05:51.553
-You keep busy not to think about things?
-That's right. You stay busy.

01:05:51.620 --> 01:05:53.696
Keep your mind on your working and stuff.

01:05:53.763 --> 01:05:56.276
And don't focus on
the bad things in your life.

01:05:56.343 --> 01:05:58.813
I'll be 84 on the 16th of April.

01:05:58.880 --> 01:06:00.673
How do you stay in such good shape?

01:06:00.740 --> 01:06:03.219
Oh I'll tell you what I blame it on.

01:06:03.286 --> 01:06:05.112
I've worked beyond the call of duty.

01:06:05.179 --> 01:06:07.703
I mean I've worked hard all my life.

01:06:07.770 --> 01:06:10.289
And I blame it on that.
It's just staying in shape.

01:06:10.356 --> 01:06:13.943
-So you think just whatever your pain,
whatever bad things happen in life,

01:06:14.010 --> 01:06:15.699
just drive through it with work?

01:06:15.766 --> 01:06:17.873
Or do you think that's a coping mechanism,

01:06:17.940 --> 01:06:20.883
that you actually have to
do the time and sit through it?

01:06:20.950 --> 01:06:23.856
I set myself up no matter what happened,

01:06:23.923 --> 01:06:25.222
even losing the kid,

01:06:26.142 --> 01:06:28.000
not to grieve over it a lot.

01:06:28.067 --> 01:06:29.832
Do you understand? Keep going.

01:06:31.040 --> 01:06:32.569
I'll give you an instance.

01:06:33.040 --> 01:06:33.923
Right here,

01:06:34.407 --> 01:06:38.066
my daddy and mother had a restaurant
and a beer joint right there.

01:06:38.600 --> 01:06:41.483
One night on full moon
I walked right here right here.

01:06:41.960 --> 01:06:44.817
And I said, you know, I was talking to God.

01:06:44.884 --> 01:06:47.640
I said God what's it going to be like
when they're gone?

01:06:47.707 --> 01:06:49.022
I could see them in there.

01:06:49.089 --> 01:06:51.647
A few months later
I walked back out and stood here.

01:06:51.714 --> 01:06:54.701
The moon was full and I looked there,
they were both dead.

01:06:54.768 --> 01:06:55.913
I said now God I know.

01:06:55.980 --> 01:06:56.956
I said now

01:06:57.964 --> 01:06:59.951
the family is gonna fall on me.

01:07:00.018 --> 01:07:02.806
In other words
we counted on daddy and mother.

01:07:02.873 --> 01:07:05.696
Now the family is going…
they counted on me after that.

01:07:05.763 --> 01:07:07.928
So I had to set myself up for that.

01:07:07.995 --> 01:07:09.093
It weren't good.

01:07:09.160 --> 01:07:13.383
But it makes things
a little harder in life too, you know.

01:07:13.450 --> 01:07:14.931
How are you doing right now?

01:07:14.998 --> 01:07:16.976
Real good. I'm doing good.

01:07:17.742 --> 01:07:21.231
-I lost my wife five years ago.
-I'm sorry.

01:07:21.720 --> 01:07:22.705
But again…

01:07:23.465 --> 01:07:24.364
Uh…

01:07:24.431 --> 01:07:25.314
I keep going.

01:07:25.950 --> 01:07:26.875
I just keep going.

01:07:26.942 --> 01:07:30.203
And you got guys like Steve
you've known your whole life.

01:07:30.740 --> 01:07:33.192
-That's cool to have.
-And I got family around.

01:07:33.259 --> 01:07:35.926
My grandkids live right here.

01:07:35.993 --> 01:07:37.573
Two of them right over here.

01:07:37.640 --> 01:07:39.970
My daughter lives right up the road here.

01:07:40.037 --> 01:07:41.910
-So it's a strong community?
-Yeah.

01:07:42.353 --> 01:07:43.854
We're family people.

01:07:43.921 --> 01:07:46.814
Something happens,
you guys tribe together here no problem.

01:07:46.881 --> 01:07:48.422
[Steve] He's the first person

01:07:48.867 --> 01:07:51.192
I come to when my son got killed.

01:07:51.800 --> 01:07:53.094
He's the first person.

01:07:53.780 --> 01:07:54.797
I woke up,

01:07:55.277 --> 01:07:57.713
went a little bit of sleep
and drove over here.

01:07:57.780 --> 01:07:58.663
First person.

01:07:59.290 --> 01:08:01.977
And my question was what am I gonna do?

01:08:03.305 --> 01:08:05.283
Tell me 'cause I know he's lost a kid.

01:08:05.350 --> 01:08:08.019
You're gonna do the same thing I done.

01:08:08.086 --> 01:08:11.153
You're gonna set yourself up
to make it through it.

01:08:11.220 --> 01:08:12.819
And that's what we done.

01:08:12.886 --> 01:08:14.846
You know I'm real good.

01:08:14.913 --> 01:08:16.773
I'm still a Christian today.

01:08:16.840 --> 01:08:18.546
God is number one in my life.

01:08:19.026 --> 01:08:20.769
And I'm happy.

01:08:20.836 --> 01:08:22.503
-A good Christian.
-I'm happy.

01:08:22.570 --> 01:08:23.629
[country music]

01:08:35.230 --> 01:08:38.241
[Peter] We're pretty far.
What was that a 30-minute drive?

01:08:38.308 --> 01:08:39.765
Yeah or longer, yeah.

01:08:39.832 --> 01:08:41.418
We're a ways.

01:08:41.991 --> 01:08:43.058
There's my buggies.

01:08:43.125 --> 01:08:44.283
-You got two of them.

01:08:44.350 --> 01:08:47.039
Yeah I just put
a new fan and stuff on this one.

01:08:47.106 --> 01:08:48.683
Man does it run sweet.

01:08:50.460 --> 01:08:51.993
The buggy tour.

01:08:52.060 --> 01:08:54.588
-The grand finale here, the buggy tour.

01:08:54.655 --> 01:08:56.461
This one looks professional.

01:08:56.528 --> 01:09:00.569
This is an $80,000 swamp buggy

01:09:00.636 --> 01:09:03.338
if you had to have it built by…

01:09:03.405 --> 01:09:05.236
I'm sorry I can't remember his name.

01:09:05.303 --> 01:09:09.303
He just passed away and he was
the best buggy builder there ever was.

01:09:11.313 --> 01:09:12.493
What do you think?

01:09:12.560 --> 01:09:13.619
Let's do it Steve.

01:09:14.020 --> 01:09:15.319
We're gonna have

01:09:16.026 --> 01:09:17.773
a beautiful time.

01:09:18.884 --> 01:09:20.098
[engine starts]

01:09:21.185 --> 01:09:24.057
-[Steve scoffs]
-[Peter laughing] Oh he just got hosed on.

01:09:24.124 --> 01:09:25.386
-Musta rained down here.

01:09:25.460 --> 01:09:27.931
-It don't look it though, does it?
-No. No.

01:09:29.270 --> 01:09:31.533
Steve, what got you into the buggy tours?

01:09:31.600 --> 01:09:33.637
I worked for the National Park Service

01:09:34.094 --> 01:09:38.886
and there was never ever
a swamp buggy tour in the Big Cypress.

01:09:39.410 --> 01:09:40.653
They never allowed it.

01:09:40.720 --> 01:09:43.366
Not saying that people didn't do it though.

01:09:43.433 --> 01:09:45.357
Sneak in and carry people.

01:09:46.310 --> 01:09:48.046
But I was working for them

01:09:48.760 --> 01:09:51.523
and they was talking about
starting a swamp buggy tour.

01:09:51.590 --> 01:09:53.133
I loved it. I love buggying.

01:09:53.200 --> 01:09:54.613
I just love buggying man.

01:09:54.680 --> 01:09:55.953
I love them woods.

01:09:56.020 --> 01:10:00.165
Right now it's dry season
so of course we're not gonna see no water

01:10:00.232 --> 01:10:01.879
but it's beautiful out here.

01:10:02.626 --> 01:10:04.893
That's an air plant. It's a bromeliad.

01:10:04.960 --> 01:10:06.801
It just attaches itself to the tree.

01:10:06.868 --> 01:10:10.149
It doesn't grow in
and it just don't hurt anything.

01:10:10.723 --> 01:10:12.620
It's like its own little ecosystem.

01:10:12.686 --> 01:10:13.573
Right.

01:10:13.640 --> 01:10:16.754
And the pine trees you see
are called slash pines.

01:10:17.549 --> 01:10:19.352
-So this fills in with water?

01:10:19.419 --> 01:10:21.048
Oh it'll be knee deep.

01:10:21.115 --> 01:10:22.306
-Knee deep?
-Knee deep.

01:10:22.373 --> 01:10:23.641
That's why we're so high?

01:10:23.708 --> 01:10:26.943
That's why we gotta
build the buggies high and tall like this.

01:10:27.010 --> 01:10:28.927
-And this is coral reef down here?
-No.

01:10:28.994 --> 01:10:30.497
-What is it?
-It's limestone.

01:10:30.564 --> 01:10:31.963
We call it cap rock.

01:10:32.030 --> 01:10:34.233
But this was underwater at one time.

01:10:34.300 --> 01:10:35.534
10,000 years ago.

01:10:35.601 --> 01:10:37.425
-10000 years?
-It was all ocean.

01:10:38.312 --> 01:10:39.911
This is where it's at Steve.

01:10:39.978 --> 01:10:43.500
Put the feet out
sit back in the comfortable chair,

01:10:44.864 --> 01:10:46.570
drift through the Everglades.

01:10:47.387 --> 01:10:50.343
-Are you comfortable?
-I'm getting super comfortable, Steve.

01:10:50.410 --> 01:10:52.614
I got five pounds in each one of my tires.

01:10:52.681 --> 01:10:56.124
-Where it rides real soft over these rocks.
-Yeah, super smooth.

01:10:56.191 --> 01:10:59.205
[Peter] I've taken a love
to the Everglades. Big Cypress.

01:10:59.272 --> 01:11:00.193
-Why?

01:11:00.260 --> 01:11:04.323
'Cause first impressions,
it's not that impressive to be honest.

01:11:04.390 --> 01:11:05.915
Once you spend a little time

01:11:07.173 --> 01:11:08.643
it starts to come out.

01:11:08.710 --> 01:11:10.488
Clyde Butcher says it.

01:11:10.555 --> 01:11:11.685
He's a friend of mine.

01:11:11.752 --> 01:11:15.445
We've worked together
on raising money for the Fakahatchee.

01:11:15.891 --> 01:11:18.152
He said you can drive by it every day.

01:11:18.623 --> 01:11:20.647
Until you stop and get off in it

01:11:21.280 --> 01:11:23.084
you don't know about the Everglades.

01:11:23.151 --> 01:11:24.035
-Yeah exactly.

01:11:24.102 --> 01:11:26.249
I mean you ride up and down 41

01:11:26.934 --> 01:11:29.560
but until you get on a buggy

01:11:30.060 --> 01:11:32.996
and walk or get to ride with me

01:11:33.063 --> 01:11:35.337
with a person
that's born and raised in it

01:11:35.404 --> 01:11:39.613
and can explain
all the different things to you,

01:11:39.680 --> 01:11:41.423
it ain't no fun.

01:11:41.490 --> 01:11:44.273
-It's old Florida.
-Old Florida.

01:11:44.340 --> 01:11:46.053
Which is almost gone right?

01:11:46.120 --> 01:11:47.075
Almost gone.

01:11:47.142 --> 01:11:49.436
This little corner of it is holding on.

01:11:49.959 --> 01:11:51.548
-Forever.
-Forever.

01:11:51.615 --> 01:11:53.838
-'Cause it's protected.
-Because it's a park.

01:11:53.905 --> 01:11:55.648
-National park.
-Yeah.

01:11:56.102 --> 01:11:58.860
If it wasn't we'd be Walmart.

01:11:58.927 --> 01:12:01.337
We'd be pulling up here
to get a 12-pack of beer.

01:12:01.404 --> 01:12:03.473
-Right.
-There's a bromeliad growing.

01:12:05.387 --> 01:12:06.858
Look there's the prairie.

01:12:08.860 --> 01:12:11.036
-Oh yeah.
-This is…

01:12:11.103 --> 01:12:12.574
[Peter sighs with relief]

01:12:12.641 --> 01:12:13.524
[silence]

01:12:26.190 --> 01:12:28.787
[Peter] That's a special thing huh?
In a loud world.

01:12:28.854 --> 01:12:31.167
-What you just done is special.

01:12:31.750 --> 01:12:33.983
That's why I love the Everglades.

01:12:34.050 --> 01:12:36.523
The Everglades is millions of acres.

01:12:36.590 --> 01:12:40.266
And the Everglades runs from
Disney World, south.

01:12:40.333 --> 01:12:43.910
You know all that expansion
all the way down to here

01:12:43.977 --> 01:12:46.180
to the Keys is the Everglades.

01:12:46.680 --> 01:12:47.739
Millions of acres.

01:12:48.479 --> 01:12:49.362
It's water.

01:12:50.210 --> 01:12:52.542
Water is what it's all about.

01:12:54.130 --> 01:12:55.933
Purifying water.

01:12:56.000 --> 01:12:58.957
The Everglades is a giant water filter.

01:13:00.206 --> 01:13:03.671
Millions of people get their water
from underneath the ground here.

01:13:04.367 --> 01:13:05.563
Millions.

01:13:05.630 --> 01:13:07.309
Miami feeds off of it.

01:13:07.900 --> 01:13:10.093
You know that's why it's so important

01:13:10.803 --> 01:13:12.403
to save the Everglades.

01:13:13.045 --> 01:13:14.887
Like all this runoff.

01:13:15.590 --> 01:13:17.988
See, the big Cypress is a big bowl.

01:13:18.590 --> 01:13:21.991
We don't get no water
from Lake Okeechobee,

01:13:22.058 --> 01:13:25.133
and Lake Kissimmee,
and all the farm runoffs.

01:13:25.200 --> 01:13:28.121
We don't get that. It's all rain.

01:13:28.750 --> 01:13:30.616
The water that comes out of here,

01:13:30.683 --> 01:13:34.158
even the water that comes down
from Lake Okeechobee,

01:13:34.225 --> 01:13:36.192
and feeds through the sawgrass,

01:13:36.259 --> 01:13:38.071
it all goes out to the Gulf.

01:13:38.960 --> 01:13:42.505
And at the same time that's happening
the good Lord has made it

01:13:43.027 --> 01:13:46.610
to where fish
have their spawn at that time.

01:13:46.677 --> 01:13:48.229
So this brings out

01:13:48.296 --> 01:13:51.432
little microbes
for the small fish to eat on.

01:13:53.010 --> 01:13:54.423
So it all works.

01:13:54.940 --> 01:13:55.823
And it's just…

01:13:56.460 --> 01:14:00.584
It goes one inch every mile
from the Gulf north.

01:14:01.080 --> 01:14:02.798
That's how far the ground goes up.

01:14:02.865 --> 01:14:05.150
It's like one inch a mile.

01:14:05.217 --> 01:14:06.673
It's a little lean.

01:14:06.740 --> 01:14:08.713
You know what it is too Steve?

01:14:08.780 --> 01:14:10.803
The sky here. The clouds.

01:14:10.870 --> 01:14:14.519
This is one of the only national parks

01:14:15.009 --> 01:14:17.050
that's a night sky park.

01:14:18.170 --> 01:14:20.813
I do nighttime afternoon tours.

01:14:20.880 --> 01:14:25.001
When it gets dark if there ain't
no clouds in the sky or a fire burning,

01:14:26.560 --> 01:14:29.472
you can reach up and pick a star.

01:14:29.946 --> 01:14:30.844
-Yeah.

01:14:30.911 --> 01:14:32.215
-It's unbelievable.

01:14:32.282 --> 01:14:33.580
It's unbelievable.

01:14:36.270 --> 01:14:40.967
…the Chokoloskee, first thing he does
is open his window to smell the mud.

01:14:41.410 --> 01:14:43.976
And I told him I said
Stevie does the same thing

01:14:44.043 --> 01:14:45.783
when we come over that bridge.

01:14:45.850 --> 01:14:48.859
She rolls that window down
and smells that mud.

01:14:48.926 --> 01:14:50.043
I sure do.

01:14:50.110 --> 01:14:52.716
[Peter] You're in Chicago
but you're gonna move back.

01:14:52.783 --> 01:14:54.763
I'm in Chicago but I'm moving back.

01:14:54.830 --> 01:14:57.183
You can't help yourself but come back.

01:14:57.250 --> 01:15:00.352
-Stevie what does it look like
around you right now?

01:15:00.419 --> 01:15:02.019
-The streets?
-[Stevie giggles]

01:15:02.570 --> 01:15:05.063
-This is what it looks like.
-There we go.

01:15:05.130 --> 01:15:06.303
It's about 38 degrees.

01:15:06.370 --> 01:15:09.358
So it's kind of warm
for up here but still cold.

01:15:09.883 --> 01:15:13.085
She misses me.
I miss my baby. That's my baby.

01:15:13.152 --> 01:15:15.535
-Steve's a good time, as you know.

01:15:15.602 --> 01:15:18.618
I usually call and talk to him
every day around this time.

01:15:18.685 --> 01:15:20.593
-Every day.
-But I'll let you have him.

01:15:20.660 --> 01:15:22.898
Okay. I can take a moment.

01:15:22.965 --> 01:15:25.984
-I can go chill over there.
-No, we don't mind.

01:15:26.051 --> 01:15:28.019
I love you Stevie. I miss you.

01:15:28.086 --> 01:15:30.549
-I love you Dad. Call me when you get home.
-Okay.

01:15:30.616 --> 01:15:31.851
-All right. Bye.
-Bye.

01:15:32.412 --> 01:15:33.469
That's my baby.

01:15:36.680 --> 01:15:38.033
Can I talk about you?

01:15:38.100 --> 01:15:40.750
-You want to talk about me?
-I want to talk about you.

01:15:40.817 --> 01:15:41.711
Go for it.

01:15:41.779 --> 01:15:44.807
Well Peter, I greatly appreciate

01:15:45.656 --> 01:15:46.689
what you've done.

01:15:47.455 --> 01:15:50.503
And I want to tell you
from the bottom of my heart

01:15:51.651 --> 01:15:55.258
I want to thank you because
you have helped me with my business.

01:15:55.760 --> 01:15:58.239
I was having a hard time. I really was.

01:15:59.030 --> 01:16:01.935
I mean I was making it
but I wasn't making it.

01:16:02.002 --> 01:16:04.068
You know summer's coming along.

01:16:04.490 --> 01:16:05.725
I got a lot of bills.

01:16:06.353 --> 01:16:09.239
And without…
If you wouldn't have helped me

01:16:09.306 --> 01:16:12.550
I would have had to
end up selling my Jeep or something

01:16:12.617 --> 01:16:14.038
to get through the summer.

01:16:14.105 --> 01:16:17.017
-From the last video?
-From the last video that you made.

01:16:17.084 --> 01:16:18.353
-Okay.
-Really helped.

01:16:18.420 --> 01:16:20.748
Well that was just luck. We ran into you.

01:16:20.815 --> 01:16:23.941
I mean it was luck,
whatever you want to call it.

01:16:24.008 --> 01:16:25.758
I say it was God sent.

01:16:25.825 --> 01:16:29.902
Because the good Lord knows
that I'm trying to do good.

01:16:30.402 --> 01:16:31.663
I really am.

01:16:31.730 --> 01:16:34.153
Trying to get by and you come along.

01:16:34.220 --> 01:16:36.388
I wasn't gonna do it, Peter.

01:16:36.468 --> 01:16:37.706
I wasn't gonna do it.

01:16:38.867 --> 01:16:42.461
That's when I asked you how many people
and you said a couple thousand.

01:16:42.528 --> 01:16:44.003
Then I thought in my brain

01:16:44.070 --> 01:16:46.716
well you know what,
I wish somebody would help me.

01:16:46.783 --> 01:16:49.342
So maybe if I put him
on a buggy ride and helped him

01:16:49.409 --> 01:16:51.493
he'll get more people watching, you know?

01:16:51.560 --> 01:16:54.594
So then I said
come on hop on the buggy. Let's go.

01:16:54.661 --> 01:16:59.536
'Cause I was thinking of you. I didn't know
you have over four million viewers

01:16:59.603 --> 01:17:01.933
and God the people started calling.

01:17:02.000 --> 01:17:06.338
And it's like I told my daughter
I said I can't even believe this.

01:17:06.405 --> 01:17:10.681
And somebody tells me, "Steve, you know
how many people that watch his videos?"

01:17:10.748 --> 01:17:13.233
No I don't know nothing about YouTube.

01:17:13.674 --> 01:17:15.981
But man, you're the best, Peter.

01:17:16.048 --> 01:17:18.633
-You're the best.
-No, Steve, you're the best.

01:17:18.700 --> 01:17:21.189
People loved you and I got so many messages

01:17:21.607 --> 01:17:23.861
and like,
you got to meet up with Steve again.

01:17:23.928 --> 01:17:26.907
And I love to be able to promote

01:17:27.571 --> 01:17:30.995
a local small business from a guy like you

01:17:31.687 --> 01:17:34.833
that lives and eats,
and breathes, the thing.

01:17:34.900 --> 01:17:37.757
-So my pleasure, Steve.
-You know what else I want to say?

01:17:37.824 --> 01:17:39.535
-I want to thank the people.
-Yeah.

01:17:39.602 --> 01:17:41.350
I want to thank all of you

01:17:41.431 --> 01:17:44.314
that has booked with me
and watched his videos

01:17:44.381 --> 01:17:46.457
and called me, I've had a lot of calls.

01:17:46.524 --> 01:17:48.833
Call my home. Call my office number.

01:17:48.900 --> 01:17:52.293
And if you just want to
ask about some questions I don't mind.

01:17:52.360 --> 01:17:55.391
About 6:00 to 9:00 at night
'cause I go to bed early

01:17:55.831 --> 01:17:57.022
and I'm always at home.

01:17:57.089 --> 01:17:59.413
You sure you want your number out there?

01:17:59.480 --> 01:18:01.503
Well yeah. I want people to call me.

01:18:01.570 --> 01:18:03.836
If you want something like this yourself

01:18:04.403 --> 01:18:05.920
link is down below.

01:18:06.590 --> 01:18:08.533
Give Steve a call or an email.

01:18:08.600 --> 01:18:09.723
Set it up.

01:18:09.790 --> 01:18:12.976
Other Everglades videos,
I'm gonna put them around here.

01:18:13.043 --> 01:18:14.337
Steve you're the best.

01:18:14.922 --> 01:18:17.022
-Appreciate you brother.
-Thank you, Peter.

01:18:17.089 --> 01:18:19.591
I really appreciate it guys.
Thank y'all very much.

01:18:19.658 --> 01:18:22.779
-Thanks for coming on that journey.
-And God bless all of you.

01:18:22.846 --> 01:18:24.133
Until the next one.

01:18:24.200 --> 01:18:25.259
[country music]

